(53, 49, 'Wave', '0', '0', '0', 'Wave_Fluted_Flat_Coulters_3.png', '<p>There are a number of styles of wavy/fluted coulters. The more waves on a coulter, the more it tills or fluffs the soil. Lower wave designs are ideal for minimum soil disturbance while higher wave designs leave a finely tilled seedbed.</p>', '<p><strong><span style="font-size: medium;">8 WAVE</span></strong></p>\r\n<table class="diameter" style="width: 100%;" border="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DIAMETER&nbsp;(INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>THICKNSS (INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>BUNDLE SIZE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>16&rdquo; to 22&rdquo;</strong></td>\r\n<td>3 to 5 mm</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>13 WAVE</strong></span></p>\r\n<table class="diameter" style="width: 100%; height: 20px;" border="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DIAMETER&nbsp;(INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>THICKNSS (INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>BUNDLE SIZE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>13&rdquo; to 20&rdquo;</strong></td>\r\n<td>3 to 5 mm</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>25 WAVE</strong></span></p>\r\n<table class="diameter" style="width: 100%;" border="1">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DIAMETER&nbsp;(INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>THICKNSS (INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>BUNDLE SIZE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>13&rdquo; to 20&rdquo;</strong></td>\r\n<td>3 to 5 mm</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Center Hole Config.jpg', 0),
(54, 49, 'Bubble', '0', '0', '0', 'Bubble_Flat_Coulters_1.png', '<p><span>Bubble coulters have sharp leading edges that cut residue and push it aside to spread the soil open. This type of coulter works best in sandy soils and dry conditions.</span></p>', '<p><strong><span style="font-size: medium;">18 WAVE</span></strong></p>\r\n<table class="diameter" style="width: 100%;" border="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DIAMETER&nbsp;(INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>THICKNSS (INCH)</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>BUNDLE SIZE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>16&rdquo;</strong></td>\r\n<td>3 to 5 mm</td>\r\n<td>100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Center Hole Config.jpg', 0),
(55, 50, 'Plain', '0', '0', '0', 'plain_Myco_TerrAne_3.png', '<p>These discs are ideal for use in all types of Soil Conditions. The disc performs exceptionally well in very Abrasive soil types and the self sharpening edge gives a very effective cutting action to the disc resulting in deeper soil penetration and improved trash cutting. The deep flutes give extra wearing capacity compared to other types of discs. These Discs also work very well in moist and stick soils.</p>\r\n<p>We offer a full line of Myco-terrane blades in various grades of steel (Myco-Boron , Stainless Steel, Carbon 1070, carbon 1080 and Chrome Steel), sizes and&nbsp;concavities as per your tillage requirement. Browse our selection of Myco-terrane disc blades below, or contact us for customized blades.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Advantages:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As the disc wears, the edge becomes more aggressive and therefore improves disc self-sharpening.</p>', '<table class="diameter" style="width: 100%;" border="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DIAMETER (INCHINSERT INTO `product_detail_level3` (`level3_id`, `product_menu_level2_id`, `product_menu3`, `spanish_images`, `rhino_images`, `tiger_images`, `product_menu_image`, `description`, `specification_detail`, `pdf`, `enable`) VALUES
(65, 56, 'Disc plough', '0', '0', '0', 'Disc_Harrow_Disc_Plough.png', '<p>The disc plough is the perfect tool when ploughing uneven ground that has obstacles and buried rocks. It helps break up undisturbed soil by inverting it to bury surface weeds and trash. Regular use of disc ploughs reduces soil aggregates to small particles and produces a compacted layer or plough pan which prevents air, water or roots penetrating the subsoil.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ADVANTAGES</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Excellent solution for rooty, sticky or abrasive soil.</li>\r\n<li>Adjustable disc position angle for use in tough or soft soil conditions.</li>\r\n<li>Adjustable and replaceable scrapers not only for cleaning also for overturning</li>\r\n</ul>', '<table class="diameter" style="height: 387px; width: 100%;" border="1" align="center">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><span>SIZE</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>2 BOTTOM</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>3 BOTTOM</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>4 BOTTOM</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>5 BOTTOM (4+1)</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><span>FRAME</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><span>Extra Heavy Duty Tubular Frame (OD 168 mm, ID 146 mm)</span></td>\r\n<td><span>Extra Heavy Duty Tubular Frame (OD 168 mm, ID 146 mm)</span></td>\r\n<td><span>Extra Heavy Duty Tubular Frame (OD 168 mm, ID 146 mm)</span></td>\r\n<td><span>Extra Heavy Duty Tubular Frame (OD 168 mm, ID 146 mm)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><span>MOUNTED</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><span>CAT &ndash; II</span></td>\r\n<td><span>CAT &ndash; II</span></td>\r\n<td><span>CAT &ndash; II</span></td>\r\n<td><span>CAT &ndash; II</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>LENGTH</strong></td>\r\n<td><span>1800 mm</span></td>\r\n<td><span>2400 mm</span></td>\r\n<td><span>3000 mm</span></td>\r\n<td><span>3600 mm</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><strong><span>WIDTH</span></strong></strong></td>\r\n<td><span>820 mm</span></td>\r\n<td><span>1040 mm</span></td>\r\n<td><